<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPPERS-NOTES-LBPT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLOSS WALKS OUT ON SESSION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Keith Closs, who seems to prefer zigging when zagging is
recommended, just left Wednesday when he was required to lift.
</P>
<P>
   So, on the strength of his latest backpedal from, the Clippers'
7-foot-3 backup center may not be in uniform for Friday's game with
the Minnesota Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
   Here's the skinny:
</P>
<P>
   Closs, who goes about 215 pounds on days when he tells the
Mickey D's drive-through captain to ``super-size it,'' bugged out
of a mandatory weight-lifting session following Wednesday's
practice at Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   His departure was witnessed by Coach Chris Ford, who peeled away
from his post-practice chat with reporters to confront the
third-year Clipper. But Closs, who said he had to attend a meeting,
kept walking.
</P>
<P>
   Ford said Closs would not suit up when the T'Wolves hit Staples
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   A Closs-free zone will disappoint Clipper fans, who wildly
cheered him during Monday's 25-minute, 13-point, 7-rebound effort
vs. San Antonio. Closs, who appears to have a lease in Ford's
doghouse, was summoned just three minutes into that game, because
starting center Michael Olowokandi had just acquired his second
personal foul.
</P>
<P>
   Olowokandi stayed out of foul trouble Tuesday in Sacramento,
producing 14 points and 15 rebounds. Closs played just six minutes
and didn't score.
</P>
<P>
   Fast breaks: Wednesday was day one on the 10-day contract of
latest Clipper Pete Chilcutt. The 6-10 forward, whose NBA journey
has lasted nine years, averaged 1.8 points and 1.7 rebounds in 26
games this season with the Utah Jazz. ``I don't really know what to
expect,'' said Chilcutt of his Clipper role. ... While most of the
Clippers spent Wednesday's working running and shooting, Maurice
Taylor, Lamar Odom, Derek Anderson and Olowokandi received
treatment for an assortment of aches and pains. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-20-00 0002EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
