<HEADLINE>
USC NEEDED THE REST 
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   It's been eight days since USC's emotional victory over UCLA,
but Trojans coach Henry Bibby welcomed the layoff as a chance for
his team to catch its breath and regroup.
</P>
<P>
   ``It gives guys that have played a lot of minutes time to
recover,'' Bibby said. ``The stretch we go through now will have a
bearing on us, if we don't watch what we do in practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, practices are not as tough because guys are playing
so many minutes.''
</P>
<P>
   With five starters averaging more than 30 minutes a game, Bibby
said he is still not worried about fatigue.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it's a problem,'' Bibby said. ``A day between
games is ample enough time to get your legs back again.''
</P>
<P>
   No repeat: One thing the Trojans (10-5, 3-0) are trying to a
void is a repeat of last year's tailspin, when they lost six
straight conference games after a 2-1 start.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't do anything like last year,'' forward Sam Clancy
said. ``We're trying to win all our home games, and split our road
games but our goal is not to lose two in a row.''
</P>
<P>
   Clancy doesn't anticipate any prolonged losing streaks.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're playing as a team a lot better than at any time last
season,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   House vs. Trepagnier: The featured matchup in today's game will
occur when USC's Jeff Trepagnier tries to contain Arizona State
guard Eddie House, the leading scorer in the Pacific-10 Conference
at 24.4 points per game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to have to run him around a little bit and try to
get him tired,'' House told the Arizona Republic. ``I think I'll
take away from his offen se by him focusing so much on guarding
me.''
</P>
<P>
   Bibby admitted that there are only so many options in stopping
House.
</P>
<P>
   ``How do you play a guy who shoots 35 times is not looking to
pass a lot ?'' Bibby said. ``Is he ever looking to pass? Only when
he's double-teamed or out of bounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know how you play him. He poses a lot of problems.''
</P>
<P>
   House did not enjoy great success last season against the
Trojans. He was 4 for 18 from the field in two games and scored 16
points.
</P>
<P>
   Overlooked recruit: Arizona State freshman point guard Kyle Dodd
has just three turnovers in his past seven games. Dodd, who attende
d Brea-Olinda High, was interested in USC, but was dropped from
consideration by the Trojans and committed to the Sun Devils.
</P>
</TEXT>
