<P>
   KRACE (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Rep. David Haley is expected to
introduce a racial profiling bill; it would require all law
enforcement agencies in Kansas to compile annual reports of all
stops, including those for traffic violations, and to include
racial and gender characteristics of those detained; the
information would go to the AG, who would report results to the
Legislature. The idea is to get reliable data that will show
whether minorities are stopped in disproportionate numbers. By John
A. Dvorak. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
