verdict stemmed from a 1997 rail crossing accident that crippled a
Sedalia woman. The $160 million verdict was among the 10 largest in
the United States last year. Though he reduced the verdict, Judge
Charles Atwell blasted Union Pacific, saying it did virtually
nothing to ensure crossing safety. By Joe Lambe. Story will move in
the ``a'' category.
