   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   SKUBE-ON-BOOKS _ Ian Frazier, in his new book ``On the Rez''
(Knopf, $25), follows in a long, often illustrious line of writers
whose sympathy for the Indian becomes a kind of personal search.
Frazier wants to BE an Indian; he wants, in particular, to be a
member of the Oglala Sioux, one of the Great Plains tribes that
joined almost on impulse one day in the summer of 1876 to defeat
Custer in the Battle of the Little Big Horn. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 32.
