   BOOK-NOTES _ Sure, everyone knows professional wrestling
attracts millions of fans. We just didn't know they could read.
This week, however, Mike Foley's autobiography, ``Have a Nice
Day,'' is solidly pinned in the No. 5 spot on the New York Times
best seller list between Frank McCourt's ```Tis'' and David
Maraniss' Vince Lombardi bio, ``When Pride Still Mattered.'' In
