<HEADER>
A1525 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-STYLE-SLIDES23-COX     01-20 0349
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-SLIDES23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Next best thing to barefoot: cool your heels in a bright pair of
feminine, sexy slides
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Jan. 23
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you're bound for a resort vacation, pack along a pair of
barely there sandals.
</P>
<P>
   Considered one of the oldest types of footwear, sandals were
first made from woven palm leaves and grasses or treated hide.
</P>
<P>
   Today the term refers to any shoe that leaves a large part of
the foot bare. Slides and mules _ most fashion pros use the terms
interchangeably _ fit comfortably into this category. Both styles
bare the heels and come in various guises, including open-toed,
strapped and thong styles.
</P>
<P>
   Thongs are sandals held to the foot with narrow strips of
leather or fabric running between the first and second toes and
attached at either side. Mules generally cover the toes. And slides
are so named because they slide right on.
</P>
<P>
   Slides have been popular for the past several seasons, but never
before have they looked as feminine as this year.
</P>
<P>
   ``They are pretty and colorful with all types of trims,'' says
Sheila Kamensky, fashion director of Rich's stores, ``including
flowers and bows as well as colorful beads and rhinestones.''
</P>
<P>
   Most slides and mules are pancake flat, with a few rising on
half-inch-to-1-inch wedge, straight or curvy heels.
</P>
<P>
   Handbag designer Kate Spade recently debuted her line of shoes,
in which thongs and slides rule. ``I wanted simple, versatile,
nonserious shoes to take on a beach vacation,'' says Spade.
</P>
<P>
   Her styles include double-duty silk, canvas, leather and satin
sandals that can easily be worn with a T-shirt and a pair of capri
pants during the day or a silky slip dress at night.
</P>
<P>
   Other slides are made of spring's most popular fabric: denim.
Instead of wearing these with your jeans, you might want to wear
them with khaki trousers or a simple white dress.
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-20-00 1700EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
