<P>
   COKE _ The Coca-Cola Co. is creating two divisions to manage its
European operations, the latest in a series of moves by Doug Daft,
the company's incoming chairman and chief executive officer. The
Atlanta-based company said a West Europe Group based in Madrid,
Spain, will be headed by Jose Nunez Cervera, chief of the company's
operations in Spain and Portugal. A new Central Europe and Eurasia
Group based in Vienna will be headed by Cem M. Kozlu, who has been
responsible for Turkey, Caucasus and central Asian republics.
(Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   HDEPOT-WHIRLPOOL _ Home Depot has pulled the plug on its
Whirlpool appliance line. The nation's No. 1 maker of home
appliances apparently isn't able to fulfill Home Depot's stringent
stocking needs. The companies say they are ``continuing to discuss
options'' and foresee a long-term relationship. Whirlpool had
shipping problems last year when it began converting to SAP.
Company officials deny that computer problems are to blame in Home
Depot's case. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-SURCHARGE _ Delta, United and American match Continental's
$20 fuel surcharge on fares. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERNCO _ Southern Co. met Wall Street expectations Thursday
by reporting fourth quarter net income of $123 million, after $20
million in one-time expenses, and wrapped up 1999 with record
profits. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
