<P>
   CENSUS-KICKOFF (Unalakleet, Alaska) _ Stanton Katchatag, an
82-year-old Inuit, answered a knock on his door here today at 10:50
a.m. and found Kenneth Prewitt, the director of the Census Bureau.
Pulling out the census short form he asked Katchatag his age, race
and the correct spelling of his name. The short interview here
began the first census of the new century, an effort to count the
U.S. population and find out where every one of the estimated 275
million Americans are living on April 1. By Steven A. Holmes. (With
map.)
</P>
