 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Columbus, Ga. _ The Springer Opera House presents August
Wilson's ``Fences'' in celebration of Martin Luther King Jr. Unity
Week. Performances are 8 p.m. Thursday through Saturday and Jan.
26-29; and 2:30 p.m. Sunday. 706-327-3688.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Jekyll Island, Ga. _ The third annual Jekyll Island Historic
District Open House and Festival on Saturday features free tours of
restored ``millionaire's cottages,'' vendors and entertainment.
1-877-453-5955. Also, the ninth annual Safe Harbor Winter Antiques
Show and Sale, featuring more than 30 dealers, will be held at the
Jeykll Island Hotel Saturday and Sunday. 1-800-535- 9547.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Augusta, Ga. _ The Augusta Futurity, opening Friday and
continuing through Jan. 29, is a top cutting-horse event, with a
festival including western dance, quarter horse sale, cattle drive,
exhibitors of western wear, jewelry and tack. 706-823-3417,
www.augustafuturity.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Wilmington, N.C. _ The Cape Fear Model Railroad Club's fourth
annual show Saturday and Sunday features model railroad layouts and
dealers showing their wares. 910-270-2696.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Newport News, Va. _ The Wildlife Arts Festival Saturday and
Sunday features more than 40 of the East Coast's top wildlife
artists. Hundreds of paintings, sculptures, carvings, stained
glass, jewelry and photography will be exhibited and sold.
757-595-1900.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tiptonville, Tenn. _ Reelfoot Lake State Park's Eagle Watch,
through March 12, includes guided tours of Reelfoot Lake State Park
to view the largest wintering population of bald eagles in the
eastern United States and migrating waterfowl. 901-253-7756; www.
eaglewatch.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lake Charles, La. _ Mardi Gras of Imperial Calcasieu, through
March 7, includes a parade, costumers, screams of ``Throw me
something, mister!''; also, gumbo cook-off, Cajun dancing.
1-800-456-7952.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Guntersville, Ala. _ Eagle Awareness Weekends continue
Friday-Sunday and Jan. 28-30. View wintering bald eagles at Lake
Guntersville and Joe Wheeler state parks; presentations on birds of
prey. 256-571-5444.
</P>
<P>
   _Paula Crouch Thrasher
</P>
