</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-CAUCUSES (Colfax, Iowa) _ Despite the mythic status of
the Iowa caucuses, attendance is low these days. Virtually no one
turned up for the 1996 Democratic caucuses, when President Clinton
ran unopposed. By Anne E. Kornblut and Yvonne Abraham. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-CANDIDATES (Manchester, N.H.) _ If Bill Bradley is the
zen candidate, John McCain is the Jedi master, fully caffeinated,
ready to answer any question with focused intensity. By Tina
Cassidy. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-HUMOR (Hopkinton, N.H.) _ One of the clearest divides
between the GOP and Democratic candidates this time around is that,
while the donkeys can talk policy until eyes glaze, the elephants
know how to laugh. By Mary Leonard. 1250 words.
</P>
<P>
