<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, JAN. 21
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-U.N.-HELMS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Jan. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Jan.
19, about the visit of Senator Jesse Helms to the United Nations
Security Council yesterday referred incorrectly to the precedents.
Many members of foreign parliaments have addressed the council;
Helms was not the first legislator to do so.
</P>
<P>
   BC-AIR-SAFETY-NYT (moved on Friday, Jan. 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Jan. 14,
about safety rules for business aviation misstated the damage
sustained by a Learjet 60 when it went off the runway while landing
at Hyannis, Mass. The plane was extensively damaged, not destroyed.
</P>
</TEXT>
