   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; WINE  &LR; _ The California wine industry uncorked its first
comprehensive economic impact study yesterday. Label the findings
impressive.
</P>
<P>
   Wine is the leading finished agricultural product from the
nation's leading agricultural state and generates $33 billion in
annual revenues, wages and economic activity, according to a report
commissioned by the Wine Institute and the California Association
of Winegrapecq &LR;  Growers. Nationwide, the California wine industry
has a $48 billion economic impact. By Peter Sinton
</P>
