   &QL; 
 &UR; SAK  &LR; _ Bullock &AMP; Jones, an upscale clothier that has catered to San
Francisco's elite since 1853, will close next month. Saks Inc.,
which purchased Bullock &AMP; Jones in July 1998, said the Union Square
retailer did not make enough money to justify keeping it open.
After 147 years in business, the store will close its doors on
February 19. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; CNET  &LR; _ San Francisco's Cnet, an Internet hub for tech news and
gadgets, will broaden its offerings by acquiring MySimon.com, an
online comparison shopping service for a wide variety of consumer
goods.
</P>
<P>
   Cnet said yesterday that it will buy the closely held Santa
Clara company in a stock deal valued at roughly $700 million, based
on yesterday's closing price. The deal should close by the end of
the first quarter. By Kelly Zito
